1	//! Which side(s) of a workspace a command should operate on.
2	//!
3	//! - `Side` is the clap `ValueEnum` — one of `code`, `bot`.
4	//! - `Scope` is an enum:
5	//!   - `Roles(Vec<Side>)` — dual-repo workspace; the parsed
6	//!     keyword form (`code`, `bot`, `code,bot`, `bot,code`).
7	//!   - `Single(PathBuf)` — explicit single-repo mode; ignores
8	//!     `.vc-config.toml` and operates on the one repo at the
9	//!     given path. Wired up incrementally (parser lands in
10	//!     0.42.0-2, consumers in later steps).
11	//! - Helpers (`has_code`, `is_both`, etc.) reflect the `Roles`
12	//!   arm only; on `Single(_)` they all return `false` /
13	//!   `is_empty()` returns `false`. Callers that must
14	//!   distinguish modes match on the enum directly.
15	//! - See `notes/chores-07.md > --scope enum refactor (0.42.0)`
16	//!   for the migration plan, and `notes/chores-06.md > 0.41.0-4`
17	//!   for the vocabulary capture.
